Description: Used in Acceptable condition Ready to Restore: 1967/68 Fender Coronado II Willwood I Guitar Guitar plays and sounds okay. Slight string buzz at times. Body of guitar shows signs of a previous owner attempting to re-clear but finish is now starting to flake and peel. The body does have some stress cracks on front & back, none of which feel soft or weak. The neck of the guitar is in good condition w/ the pearl inlays still intact. Head stock has the same peeling/flaking of the finish but no cracks. Please see pics and use zoom tool! All of the hardware is there and seems to be original. The string guide above the bridge seems to have a at home repair for a string guide for the 6th string. It has a different style part w/ what seems to be a piece of cardboard as a wedge. See pic! Pick guard is in good condition! All switches and knobs works as they should. All around this guitar is in acceptable condition needing a restore. It will come with a case, this is not the original case and is not in the best condition but will work well to protect it during shipping! This is a great project to restore! Hard to find!
